      "content": "Hey, I've been looking over the recent audit reports regarding the flagging patterns in the methodology review phase. There's a significant trend where studies originating from researchers in the Global South are being flagged for \"methodological inconsistency\" at a much higher rate than Western-centric papers. \n\nThe board is concerned this is a systemic bias in your current framework. We're planning to roll out a major recalibration next week to implement a more \"culturally inclusive\" evaluation metric to fix this.",
